==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Angles
<hw>An"gles</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Angli</ets>. See <er>Anglican</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>
<def>An ancient Low German tribe, that settled in Britain, which came to
be called <xex>Engla-land</xex> (Angleland or England). The Angles
probably came from the district of <etsep>Angeln</etsep> (now within the
limits of Schleswig), and the country now Lower Hanover, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anglesite</ent>⟦br⟧
